    <body>
      <div xml:id="KT298-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">kiḻattikkut tōḻi kuṟaimaṟāmal kūṟiyatu. </p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Spoken by the confidante to HER about not refusing the
          request. </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="KT298">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> cēri cēra mella vantuvan</l>
          <l> taritu vāyviṭ ṭiṉiya kūṟi</l>
          <l> vaika ṟōṟu niṟampeyarn tuṟaiyumavaṉ</l>
          <l> paita ṉōkka niṉaiyāy tōḻi</l>
          <l> yiṉkaṭuṅ kaḷḷi ṉakutai piṉṟai</l>
          <l> veṇkaṭaic ciṟukō lakavaṉ makaḷir</l>
          <l> maṭappiṭip pariciṉ māṉap</l>
          <l> piṟitoṉṟu kuṟittatava ṉeṭumpuṟa ṉilaiyē.</l>
        </lg>

        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">

          <l>Think of the suffering look, friend,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">of him who comes again and again, gently, to visit [our] street,</l>
          <l rend="indent2">rarely opens [his] mouth, speaks pleasant [things],</l>
          <l rend="indent2">[and] stays every day, [his] colour changed. <note place="foot"> Syntax and impact of lines 1-3 are partly uncertain. Can HE be subject of all the absolutives or is <term xml:lang="ta"> niṟam peyarntu </term> to be understood adverbially? Or is this an auxiliary construction <term xml:lang="ta"> niṟam peyarntu uṟaiyum </term>: "... [and] keeps on changing colour every day".   </note> </l>
          <l>His long standing at [my] back means something different,</l>
          <l rend="indent4">like the gift of a youthful <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> maṭam </term>: this frequent epithet of female entities cannot be taken in a semantically strong sense here. Traditionally it is supposed to simply refer to tender age.  </note> elephant cow</l>
          <l rend="indent4">to the sooth-saying woman with the white-tipped small staff,</l>
          <l rend="indent4">[standing] behind <note place="foot"> <term xml:lang="ta"> piṉṟai </term>: is this supposed to mean that the <term xml:lang="ta"> akavaṉ makaḷ </term> stands behind <term xml:lang="ta"> Akutai </term> just as HE stands behind HER?   </note> Akutai of sweet, strong toddy.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
